10 moles of monatomic ideal gas at $P_1 = 1.013 times 10^6$ Pa and $T_1 = 300$ K follow a cycle:
1. $(1) arrow (2)$: Linear process in P-V to $P_2 = 1.013 times 10^5$ Pa and $T_2 = 300$ K.
2. $(2) arrow (3)$: Isobaric compression to $V_3 = V_1$.
3. $(3) arrow (1)$: Isochoric process back to $P_1$.

Calculate net work. Is it performed by or on the gas?

